The @CEST_PORT@ port provides the following CMake targets:

  find_package(@Cest_ns@ @cestPackageVersion@ CONFIG REQUIRED)

  # Core — Tier A mocking with MockFn (fully portable)
  target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE @Cest_ns@::@Cest_target@)

  # Mock — Tier B hot-patching, no annotations required
  target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE @Cest_ns@::Mock)

  # MockStrict — Tier B hot-patching, requires CEST_MOCKABLE annotations
  target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE @Cest_ns@::MockStrict)

@Cest_ns@::Mock and @Cest_ns@::MockStrict transitively link
@Cest_ns@::@Cest_target@, so you do not need to list the core target
twice.

Hot-patching (Tier B) is supported on Linux and Windows in Debug builds.
For macOS or Release builds, use Tier A (MockFn) instead.